Library Management System - Project Report
1. Executive SummaryL
The Library Management System (LMS) is a robust, full-stack web application designed to streamline the operations of a modern library. It facilitates the efficient management of books, members, and borrowing transactions. The system replaces manual record-keeping with a digital, automated solution that ensures data integrity, real-time availability tracking, and a seamless user experience.

2. Objectives
Digitization: Convert physical records of books and members into a persistent digital database.
Automation: Automate the borrowing and returning process, including date tracking and quantity adjustments.
Usability: Provide a clean, modern, and responsive user interface for library staff.
Reliability: Ensure data persistence across system restarts and prevent data corruption.
3. Technology Stack
The project is built using industry-standard technologies ensuring scalability and maintainability:

Backend
Framework: Spring Boot 3.4.12 (Java 17)
Build Tool: Maven
Database: H2 Database (File-based persistence with AUTO_SERVER mode)
ORM: Hibernate / Spring Data JPA
API: RESTful Web Services
Frontend
Framework: React 18
Build Tool: Vite
Styling: Pure CSS (Modern Variables, Flexbox/Grid, Glassmorphism)
HTTP Client: Axios
Icons: Lucide React
