5. System Architecture
The application follows a standard Client-Server Architecture:

Client (Frontend): A Single Page Application (SPA) served by Vite. It consumes JSON APIs exposed by the backend to fetch data and render the UI.
Server (Backend): A Spring Boot application that handles business logic, validation, and database interactions.
Database: An embedded H2 database running in file mode (./librarydb) to store data permanently on the disk.
